{
  "texts": [
    "Further, in Section 6, motivated by the asymptotic limits of collapsing Ricci flows [LP25], we will introduce the notion of affine expanding soliton, and show that they all satisfy our Ansatz.Let π: M → B be a twisted principal N-bundle with N nilpotent and simply-connected, with twisting homomorphism ρ ∈ Hom(π 1 (B), Aut(N)).",
    "Fix a Haar measure ν on N, let |ν| be the corresponding density, and denote by Aut ±1 (N) the subgroup of automorphisms of N preserving |ν|.",
    "Recall that invariant metrics on M are determined by the data (g B, H, h), where g B is a metric on B, H is a connection on M, and h is a bundle metric on adM (Proposition 2.14).",
    "We call ∇ ad the affine connection on adM determined by H. Ansatz 3.1.",
    "For a pair (g, X) of an invariant metric g corresponding to (g B, H, h) and a (not necessarily invariant) vector field X on M, we assume:(i) H is flat and its monodromy is ρ:π 1 (B) → Aut ±1 (N); (ii)The fibres of π: M → B are minimal submanifolds and Ricci solitons with soliton constant -1/2, and ∇ ad (h -1 Ric h) = 0; (iii) X is vertical and it restricts to a soliton vector field of the fibres."
  ]
}